just_use critters.go

# label: EARLY
# role: supports feature — CRITTER_STUDIES portal + launch + elm.js proxy

V1 (2026-04-15). Lists studies from critters/studies/*.claude,
launches playable studies (currently only "cows"), proxies the
compiled elm.js from ~/showell_repos/elm-critters, and accepts
telemetry POSTs by delegating to critters.HandleSaveRecording.

Non-playable studies (mice, sort_cats) show "DSL defined; engine
not yet implemented" — the DSL files exist but the Elm engine is
currently hardcoded to the cow game. Future: one engine with the
study name as a flag.

The launch page is a near-copy of elm-critters/index.html with
two Gopher-specific changes: elm.js is loaded from /gopher/critters/elm.js,
and the saveRecording port posts to /gopher/critters/save_recording
with the study name stamped on the payload.
